MemoryConfiguration - Class in org.eclipse.nvplayout.model
MemoryConfiguration is the model for the global memory configuration view.
This model contain the global configuration, i-e : The Application Name. The Calibration Start Address. The RAM shadow Start Address. The ROM Start Address. The Eeprom Alias Start Address. The Calibration Version (Major, Minor and Subversion). The different size of memory sector (Calibration).
MemoryConfiguration() - Constructor for class org.eclipse.nvplayout.model.MemoryConfiguration
Set a global structure of the memory.
The initialization of this structure correspond to a impossible case.
